packets.tlm

Class Tlm

  • java.lang.Object
    • packets.tlm.Tlm

  • public final class Tlm
extends java.lang.Object
    FULLY DOCUMENTED. This class contains the name and value of a telemetry parameter to display in the GUI. It also contains the DataType of this parameter, to be used for parsing of telemetry CCSDS packets.
    Author:
    Joe Benassi

    • Constructor Detail

      • Tlm

        public Tlm(java.lang.String name,
   java.lang.String type,
   java.lang.String primitive,
   java.lang.String constant)
        This constructs a Tlm object with the given attributes. Contains a name identifying the value, and the value itself. There are as many Tlm objects for an App as there are qualities that can be displayed.
        Parameters:
        name - The name to display as what it represents.
        type - The data type for this parameter. For example, uint8, int15, char.
        primitive - Whether or not this should display a string. If this value starts with 's', this is deemed a String.
        constant - The name of the constant used if this is a String parameter. If this is a String parameter, the value tied to this String as defined in the Constant Definition file is used to increase the amount of bytes allocated to this. The value tied to this name represents the numerical amount of "type"s in the App's Housekeeping packet.
